article.description: St. Francis, Pa., 72, Long Island U. 56
article.headline: St. Francis, Pa., 72, Long Island U. 56
article.linkText: St. Francis, Pa., 72, Long Island U. 56
article.story: LORETTO, Pa. (AP) -- Cale Nelson scored 19 points to lead St. Francis, Pa., to a 72-56 victory over Long Island University on Saturday night. Devin Sweetney added 13 points and 11 rebounds, and Jelani Lawrence had 14 points and 10 rebounds for the Red Flash (7-21, 4-13 Northeast Conference), who won for the third time in four games since snapping a school-record 15-game losing streak. James Williams scored 27 points for Long Island (10-18, 6-11). The Red Flash led 39-32 at the half and extended its lead to as much as 22 points in the second half. The Blackbirds trailed 47-38 with 13:56 remaining before Sweetney scored six points in a 8-0 run that all but put the game out of reach.
